context: The Times is the first newspaper to have borne that name, lending it to numerous other papers around the world, including The Times of India (founded in <a0_0>1838<a0_0/>), The Straits Times (Singapore) (<a1_0>1845<a1_0/>), The New York Times (<a2_0>1851<a2_0/>), The Irish Times (<a3_0>1859<a3_0/>), Le Temps (France) (1861-1942), the Cape Times (South Africa) (<a4_0>1872<a4_0/>), the Los Angeles Times (1881), The Seattle Times (1891), The Manila Times (1898), The Daily Times (Malawi) (1900), El Tiempo (Colombia) (1911), The Canberra Times (1926), and The Times (Malta) (1935). In these countries, the newspaper is often referred to as The London Times or The Times of London.
